# Data Model

## Option (per-account dropdown values + graft buttons)
```js
{
  accountId: ObjectId,
  type: String,        // 'hairType' | 'hairColor' | ... | 'graftButton'
  label: String,       // for graftButton: "1/1", "2/2", etc.
  sortOrder: Number,
  // graftButton-only fields:
  intactHairs?: Number,
  totalHairs?: Number,
  isDefault?: Boolean,
}
```
- Referenced by ID from Patient and Surgery for filtering (e.g. admin: surgeries by tip style).
- graftButton type: same pattern as other options but with intactHairs, totalHairs, isDefault. Used on Tech Dash.
- CRUD via /api/options. Migration from AccountSettings: POST /api/options/migrate.

## User
```js
{
  username: String,       // login credential for all users
  passwordHash: String,
  roles: [String],        // ['admin', 'accountOwner', 'user'] — always an array
  accountId: ObjectId,    // null for admins without an account
  firstName: String,
  lastName: String,
  email: String,          // optional — contact info only, used for password reset
  lastActiveAt: Date,
}
```

## Account
```js
{
  ownerId: ObjectId,
  createdAt: Date,
  // Branding
  practiceName: String,
  website: String,
  phone: String,
  email: String,
  address: String,
  logoUrl: String,
}
```

## AccountSettings (legacy — being phased out)
- graftButtons and option arrays have been migrated to the **Option** table.
- If AccountSettings still exists with graftButtons, run POST /api/options/migrate to move them to Option.
- AccountSettings can be removed once all accounts are migrated.

## GlobalDefaults (single document, admin-managed — seeds new AccountSettings)
Same shape as `AccountSettings` minus `accountId`.

## Patient
```js
{
  accountId: ObjectId,
  initials: String,    // display identifier — no full name stored (privacy)
  dob: String,
  hairTypeId: ObjectId,    // ref Option
  hairColorId: ObjectId,
  hairCaliberId: ObjectId,
  skinColorId: ObjectId,
  createdAt: Date,
}
```
- Legacy: hairType, hairColor, etc. (String) kept during migration; prefer Id fields.

## Surgery
```js
{
  accountId: ObjectId,
  patientId: ObjectId,        // reference to Patient — never embed patient info on Surgery
  technicianIds: [ObjectId],
  status: String,             // 'active' | 'completed'
  graftGoal: Number,          // set on create, editable during surgery
  startedAt: Date,
  completedAt: Date,
  // Step 1 of New Surgery modal = select existing Patient or create new one
  // Step 2 = surgical details below (reference Option by ID for admin filtering):
  surgical: {
    surgeonId: ObjectId, fueDeviceId: ObjectId, fueTipStyleId: ObjectId,
    fueTipSizeId: ObjectId, holdingSolutionId: ObjectId, placingDeviceId: ObjectId,
  },
  // Legacy string fields (surgeon, fueDevice, etc.) kept during migration
  activeButtons: [{ label: String, intactHairs: Number, totalHairs: Number }],
  technicianButtonConfigs: [{ userId: ObjectId | String, labels: [String] }],
  // Per-technician, per-surgery button visibility — technicians customize which graft buttons appear on Tech Dash
  // label format: "intactHairs/totalHairs" e.g. "1/2" = 1 intact out of 2 total
  // 2/2 = perfect 2-hair graft, 0/1 = fully transected single-hair graft
  extraction: {
    startedAt: Date, completedAt: Date, timerMs: Number,
    entries: [{ label: String, intactHairs: Number, totalHairs: Number, count: Number }],
  },
  placement: {
    startedAt: Date, completedAt: Date, timerMs: Number,
    count: Number,
  },
}
```

## ActivityLog (per-button-click audit trail)
```js
{
  surgeryId: ObjectId,
  userId: ObjectId,         // technician who made the click
  accountId: ObjectId,
  action: String,          // 'extraction' | 'placement'
  payload: {               // action-specific
    // extraction: { label, intactHairs, totalHairs }
    // placement: {}
  },
  createdAt: Date,
}
```
- One record per graft button click or placement +1 click.
- Technicians see their own rolling log; doctor (account owner) sees all technicians.
- Edit or remove entries to correct errors — updates Surgery extraction/placement counts accordingly.
- CRUD via /api/surgeries/:id/activities.

## Reporting Formulas (derived from extraction.entries)

```js
const totalGrafts      = entries.reduce((s, e) => s + e.count, 0);
const totalHairs       = entries.reduce((s, e) => s + e.count * e.totalHairs, 0);
const totalIntact      = entries.reduce((s, e) => s + e.count * e.intactHairs, 0);
const transectedHairs  = totalHairs - totalIntact;
const hairTransectionRate  = totalHairs  ? transectedHairs / totalHairs  : 0;
const graftTransectionRate = totalGrafts ? entries
  .filter(e => e.intactHairs < e.totalHairs)
  .reduce((s, e) => s + e.count, 0) / totalGrafts : 0;
```
